Jefferies Hires Koopmans for European Equity Capital Markets

-- B y   L a u r a   M a r c i n e k
-- 
2011-09-12T13:09:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/jefferies-names-koopmans-co-head-europe-equity-capital-markets.html
Jefferies Group Inc. (JEF) , the
investment bank that’s been expanding since the financial
crisis, hired Reinout Koopmans as a managing director and co-
head of European  equity capital markets .  Koopmans was head of equity capital markets for natural
resources at Frankfurt-based Deutsche Bank AG, New York-based
Jefferies said today in a statement. He will be based in London
and work with David Weaver, head of European capital markets.  Jefferies has been adding managing directors from some of
the biggest banks. The firm hired Christopher Burns and Brian Chadwick from Goldman Sachs Group Inc. in August and June, and
added David Luse from Bank of America Corp. and Susan Bonsell
from Deutsche Bank.  “The addition of Reinout Koopmans is an important next
step in expanding our origination of European equity and equity-
linked underwritings,” said Benjamin Lorello, global head of
 investment banking  and capital markets at Jefferies.  To contact the reporter on this story:
